The LDAP config options allow you to set a name (firstnameAttribute and surnameAttribute) for a person, then separately assign the unique identifier for that person (usernameAttribute). Currently the group options only allow a single field (groupnameAttribute) for both these options, meaning if your groups are named after internal department codes these are displayed whenever you use the groups inside confluence. I would like to have two configurable fields which allows the unique id of the group to be different from the displayed name.

Confluence should allow to upload attachment file name containing these characters (&, +, ?, | or =). Currently this behavior is not allowed and the following error occurred:
{noformat}
... contains illegal characters (&, +, ?, | or =). You cannot upload files with names containing these characters.
{noformat}

